detaileddescription.para: Added to support proper decimal set/get; Decimal is the best data type to match W3C integer. This will not work with XML serializer, bc decimal types always serialize trailing zeros, and trailing zeros are not allowed with integer types TODO: Need to truncate (or possibly round) any digits after the decimal point in the setter/getter For positive/negative etc integers, need to check the sign and throw error if incorrect. May want to throw errors for for min/max allowed values also - not sure about this) May need to import System.Numerics.dll to use BigInteger
